JEENA JAMES: So laying out
a clear engagement objective

00:07:11.710 --> 00:07:15.740
is the basis on which you can
optimize the app experience.

00:07:15.740 --> 00:07:19.330
You can have plenty of ideas,
larger, smaller features

00:07:19.330 --> 00:07:21.100
that you're trying to improve.

00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:23.560
But how are you going to
identify which one actually

00:07:23.560 --> 00:07:26.040
drives user engagement?

00:07:26.040 --> 00:07:28.360
You would have to do
multiple experiments

00:07:28.360 --> 00:07:30.410
and run a lot of tests.

00:07:30.410 --> 00:07:32.680
Now, start with a hypotheses.

00:07:32.680 --> 00:07:35.900
Develop two or more
variants, and set up a test

00:07:35.900 --> 00:07:38.530
or run about a
minimum period of time

00:07:38.530 --> 00:07:41.080
so that you can get a
statistically significant

00:07:41.080 --> 00:07:42.670
result.

00:07:42.670 --> 00:07:47.180
Now, individual factors may
vary because of the use cases.

00:07:47.180 --> 00:07:51.220
So lets take a look
at it with an example.

00:07:51.220 --> 00:07:55.220
One Football, a popular
football app constantly working

00:07:55.220 --> 00:07:58.770
towards driving their engagement
goal, as Niko mentioned,

00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:01.850
uses reading more articles.

00:08:01.850 --> 00:08:04.540
With several feature
options in mind,

00:08:04.540 --> 00:08:08.170
they use Firebase
Remote Config, and that

00:08:08.170 --> 00:08:12.100
lets them change app
components on the server side,

00:08:12.100 --> 00:08:15.770
and they are not making any
updates to the app itself.

00:08:15.770 --> 00:08:18.160
They are able to test
different variations

00:08:18.160 --> 00:08:22.090
before they release the
best-performing option to all

00:08:22.090 --> 00:08:23.590
their users.

00:08:23.590 --> 00:08:25.840
Now, in this
particular experiment,

00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:27.970
they had three variations.

00:08:27.970 --> 00:08:32.620
The winning variation
saw an increase of 5%

00:08:32.620 --> 00:08:35.919
in sessions per user,
and also saw an increase

00:08:35.919 --> 00:08:41.200
of 6% in articles that
users were reading per user,

00:08:41.200 --> 00:08:44.940
as a result that variation was
rolled out to all the users.

00:08:44.940 --> 00:08:46.900
But this is a great
example of someone

00:08:46.900 --> 00:08:49.330
