00:20:32.030 --> 00:20:34.270
So let's go through some
of the main characteristics

00:20:34.270 --> 00:20:36.210
of good notification.

00:20:36.210 --> 00:20:38.290
I say notification,
but these are also

00:20:38.290 --> 00:20:41.320
applicable to other
channels of communication,

00:20:41.320 --> 00:20:42.960
like in-app messaging, e-mails.

00:20:45.660 --> 00:20:47.917
Relevance-- sounds simple.

00:20:47.917 --> 00:20:50.250
You want to send messages
that are relevant to the user,

00:20:50.250 --> 00:20:50.910
right?

00:20:50.910 --> 00:20:54.660
But it can be really hard to
find out what is relevant.

00:20:54.660 --> 00:20:57.090
So think about sending
messages that matter

00:20:57.090 --> 00:20:59.880
to the user in the
context that they are in.

00:20:59.880 --> 00:21:01.890
Be mindful of the tone you use.

00:21:01.890 --> 00:21:04.980
Be mindful of the
language that you select.

00:21:04.980 --> 00:21:08.730
Also, be creative and
true to your brand.

00:21:08.730 --> 00:21:13.110
One way of ensuring that is to
actually give them the option,

00:21:13.110 --> 00:21:16.140
to let them select
various alternatives

00:21:16.140 --> 00:21:18.810
during the onboarding flow.

00:21:18.810 --> 00:21:22.470
Actionable-- notifications
can sometimes

00:21:22.470 --> 00:21:26.760
be used to inform, and sometimes
update content, as well

00:21:26.760 --> 00:21:30.390
as allow users to
take specific actions.

00:21:30.390 --> 00:21:32.316
Whatever action or
info that you want

00:21:32.316 --> 00:21:33.690
to show in your
notification, you

00:21:33.690 --> 00:21:36.150
want to make sure that
that is also accounted

00:21:36.150 --> 00:21:40.040
for in the engagement metrics.

00:21:40.040 --> 00:21:42.990
Personalized-- we're not equal.

00:21:42.990 --> 00:21:44.290
So are your users.

00:21:44.290 --> 00:21:46.800
They are not created equal.

00:21:46.800 --> 00:21:50.570
For effective communication,
segment your user base.

00:21:50.570 --> 00:21:53.690
Create cohorts and
find customized ways

00:21:53.690 --> 00:21:56.240
to tailor your
messaging to them.

00:21:56.240 --> 00:21:59.480
Also give them options
to opt in and opt out,

00:21:59.480 --> 00:22:02.150
or filter proactively.

00:22:02.150 --> 00:22:06.770
Timeliness-- raise your
hands if you have ever

00:22:06.770 --> 00:22:10.460
received not important
messages or notifications just

00:22:10.460 --> 00:22:13.710
when you're getting to bed.

00:22:13.710 --> 00:22:17.110
OK, so right message
at the right time

00:22:17.110 --> 00:22:20.690
and at the right frequency
can drive user engagement.

00:22:20.690 --> 00:22:22.470
Consider the day of the week.

00:22:22.470 --> 00:22:24.560
Consider the time
zone that they're in.

00:22:24.560 --> 00:22:28.010
And sometimes you can also give
them one-click alternatives,

00:22:28.010 --> 00:22:30.830
like read later.

